  <mads:note type="source">Smith's Dictionary of Greek and Roman Biography and Mythology, Vol 1, 1867, p. 8: "Achaeus, 3, of 
    Eretreia, in Euboea, a tragic poet, was born B.C. 484, the year in which Aeschylus gained his first victory, and four
    years before the birth of Euripides. In B.C. 477, he contended with Sophocles and Euripides...he nevertheless gained 
    the prize only once......"</mads:note>
